@jaycarlton If you would like to catch the query output in an object but don't want to have to annotate another entity... you can use a Projection interface. It allows you to project a subset of properties from your dao into another object that isn't your actual entity.
Projection interface example here: https://github.com/all-of-us/workbench/blob/freemabd/address-comments/common-api/src/main/java/org/pmiops/workbench/cdr/model/DbMenuOption.java#L3-L3
